section.p:
The entire booktitle element content is
        displayed on the first page of the PDF, so if you need to add the information after it, in
        your customization CSS, add the
        following CSS
        rules:*[class ~= "bookmap/booktitle"]:after {
    display: block;
    content: "by " oxy_xpath('//*[contains(@class, " bookmap/bookmeta ")]/*[contains(@class, " topic/author ")]/text()');
    margin-top: 4em;
    text-align: center;
    color: gray;
}
*[class ~= "bookmap/booktitle"]:after(2) {
    display: block;
    content: oxy_xpath('if(//*[contains(@class, " bookmap/isbn ")]) then concat("ISBN ", //*[contains(@class, " bookmap/isbn ")]/text()) else ""'); 
    text-align: center;
    color: gray;
}

The entire title element content is displayed on the first page of
        the PDF, so if you need to add the information after it, in your customization CSS, add the following CSS
          rules:*[class ~= "front-page/front-page-title"] > *[class ~= "topic/title"]:after {
    display: block;
    content: "last revision " oxy_xpath('(//*[contains(@class, " map/topicmeta ")])[1] \
    //*[contains(@class, " topic/revised ")]/@modified');
    margin-top: 4em;
    text-align: center;
    color: gray;
}The [1] predicate is used to
          avoid duplicated results as the topicmeta is included in all children
          topics.

section.codeblock:
@page page-for-meta {
    background-color: yellow; /* Just to see it better*/
    @top-left-corner {
        content:""; /* Remove the default header */
    }
    @top-right-corner {
        content:""; /* Remove the default header */
    }
}

*[class ~= "bookmap/booktitle"]:after {
    page: page-for-meta;
}
*[class ~= "bookmap/booktitle"]:after(2) {
    page: page-for-meta;
}
